        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cost-effective cleaning of Dysprosium; picosecond (ps) or femtosecond reduces HAZ but increases cost. 20 ns minimizes thermal diffusion in low-conductivity metal while ablating surface layers. Source: Laser physics research on metal ablation thresholds (e.g., Appl. Surf. Sci. reviews on ns vs. ps for rare earths)."
