        "description": "Effective speeds for contaminant removal on Dysprosium; slower for heavy contamination (e.g., oxides), faster for light. Recommended 1500 mm/s optimizes fluence delivery without excessive heat buildup. Conservative for uniform coverage on soft, reflective surfaces. Source: Industry standards from laser cleaning manuals (e.g., Adapt Laser Systems) and process optimization in Opt. Lasers Eng."
